features: FROM AMERICA'S MOST TRUSTED PRINTER BRAND – Perfect for home printing, including a variety of color documents in high volumes
FULLY LOADED WITH SAVINGS – Best for low-cost, high-volume printing—up to 2 years of Original HP Ink included; get up to 6,000 black or color pages right out of the box
KEY FEATURES – Print, copy and scan, plus borderless, mobile and wireless capabilities. Print up to 10 pages per minute black and 5 pages per minute color.
HP QUALITY – Delivers color graphics and crisp text for your everyday prints
HP SMART APP – Print, scan and copy from your phone—whenever, wherever
RELIABLE CONNECTIVITY – Self-healing Wi-Fi automatically detects and resolves connection issues
SIMPLE, SPILL-FREE REFILL – Replenish ink with HP's easy-access, spill-free refill system. Simply plug the ink bottles into the ink tank and let them drain—no squeezing, no spilling.
EASY TO USE – Smart-guided buttons illuminate to guide you through everyday print, scan and copy tasks
PROTECT FROM VIRUSES AND MALWARE – HP Wolf Essential Security helps maintain privacy and control with basic encryption and password protection
SUSTAINABLE DESIGN – Made from 45% recycled plastic
body.description: The HP Smart Tank 5000 is a smart, connected and refillable tank printer that makes printing seamless for the whole family with its high capacity and wireless connectivity. Create everyday color documents at a low cost with up to 2 years of Original HP Ink included in the box.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love the InkWell rather than cartridges
reviews.reviewText: Prints well, but slowly. Each time you want to print, it takes a while to run through its set up. I use it with a MacBook Pro. I had to install the Ap to set up the printer, but it would not let me print from my graphic programs (Adobe Photoshop, Indesign, etc). HP customer service was able to help me with the problem. I had to Uninstall the Printer Driver on the Mac and then download a new driver and install it. Once I did that, the printer has worked for my graphic programs. I use a wireless connection. The colors printed are just as they should be. I do like that the inkwells are on the front of the machine so you can keep track of the ink supply.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for the price!
reviews.reviewText: Very convenient, fast printing and easy connection to my phone and laptops! Great color and easy to refill with the liquid ink!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Helpful virtual Assistant/Diagnostics
reviews.reviewText: Important: Download the 'HP Smart' app before setting up.Got this Smart Tank last month and just set it up today. Was very easy using the HP Smart app which has a step by step visual instruction for removing all the tape and stabilization inserts along with a pretty forward step by step set up.I did have a small issue with the installation of the Printer Heads. I think it was mostly my fault due to my printer table being quite low and I was sitting up higher. Anyhow..one of the heads was a tad bit off center and I couldn't perform the alignment and scan functions. I eventually used the Virtual Diagnostic in the app and it scans my printer then proceeded to give instructions to remedy the issue.Worked really well and my Printer Heads got seated properly and when I ran a print function from the printable things option a really nice crisp pic of Santa came out.Afterwards I printed out a study manuel. I Ran off about 200 sheetsflawlessly with no jams or extra blank pages from the feeder grabbing more than one sheet. I did 'Fan' my paper prior to placing on the feeder and I also only placed 30-40 sheets in at a time. The paper capacity is supposed to be 100 sheets. I'm very impressed! I like the light weight and compact size as well. Good price for a little work horse.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars It works, but it is frustrating
reviews.reviewText: The printer was pretty easy to put together, and is nice and compact. I'm not thrilled with it though because it's difficult to connect to when I'm trying to print. I don't have to print papers everyday, just maybe 1-3 times a week. Every time I go to print something, the printer is off, can't connect, doesn't have a signal etc. I find this pretty frustrating as it's advertised as a smart wireless printer. Overall it still works and prints fine, but constant disconnecting is quite annoying.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best freaking printer you will find!
reviews.reviewText: The ink lasts forever! It was definitely time for an upgrade from my old printer. This printer is reasonably priced. It comes with great instructions on how to connect it to your computer. Feels like a quality printer and doesn’t take a lot of room!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Low profile format, easy to use. Love the refill part.
reviews.reviewText: Bought this printer, as I wanted something that had refillable ink cartridges, without buying subpar ink.I believe the value for the money was good, as it was under $200, and came fully functional, with all the accessories.It seems to print quite well, the images on the documents are very clear.It could use a better interface, in that the touchscreen is very minimal, and it is an LCD, not an LED. That’s one of shortfalls, with all other actions being done through the app or through the online access.It is quite a fast printer.One downfall that I can’t seem to figure out, is Eprint. For my HP printers of the past I’ve always relied on Eprint when I’m traveling or just using my phone in the house, and send an email, with a document attached to the printer via Eprint.If there is a way to make eprint work, I could use some help.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2024
reviews.reviewText: After spending hours going through different printer reviews, I landed on this one as a final decision. Being a student, I wanted something that could help study, especially with my human anatomy course. This printer was easy to set up, connected right away, and I have had no issues printing via my Macbook either. It came with plenty of refillable ink cartridges and the color images I have printed so far are crisp and bright. Good luck on your search!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars SO easy to install and prints BEAUTIFULLY!
reviews.reviewText: I bought this just for home use and to print things for school. It is a little bigger than I expected but it was shockingly easy to install. The entire process took maybe 15 minutes. This test page I printed was just perfect. It prints a little slow but not unbearable. My only complaint is that when you aren’t using it, it makes incredibly loud clicking noises. I’m going to end up moving it out of my room or that is going to wake me up at night (hence the 4 stars). Otherwise I am incredibly happy with it! Ignore the review that complained about taking all the orange pieces out.the app walks you through and it took about 4 seconds to remove them. So far- I highly recommend this printer !

reviews.reviewTitle: Affordable good quality ink tank printer
reviews.reviewText: We have owned a few printers over the last 30 or so years. Most have been HP and we have always liked them and had good luck with print quality and features. The one sticking point has always been cartridge cost and reliability. And they have never worked well refilling them.Our last printer was a Canon and we will never buy one again. I had been watching the ink tank printers but price was the stumbling block. With the 5000 series the ink tank printers they are finally affordable.This printer makes very nice crisp prints in both letters and pictures. It does scan, the tray is direct feed from the rear top of the printer making it nice if you make water slide decals or anything similar. Super easy to set up and install the software, print heads fill tanks etc. Once on your network it just powers down and waits for the next time you tell it to print.The printer appears to be a winner and now we just have to test it for long term reliability of print heads etc. But as it stands we are impressed and do recommend this if you are tired of the small amounts of ink in cartridges and the high cost.

reviews.reviewTitle: very best printer saves lots of money for ink
reviews.reviewText: I used to have a cheap inkjet printer but thinking about how much you have to pay for ink replacement, its not that cheap. Plus, that inks get dried and clogged if you dont use it for long. The ink tank printers however is much cost efficient. I love the quality and how easy it is to set up if you have wifi at home. Dont forget to use 2.4 GHz channel when you setup at first.
